snippet.textDisplay: Lennon needs to find the right tactics to play rangers. Gerrard sussed them out. As well as the high press he made sure players were always all over the main threat players like christie, eduard and forrest. Celtic could hardly string 2 passes forward because rangers were pressing so well and left them with little options. Yet again rangers cause celtic to play bad with giving no space yet all were hearing is celtic were poor thats how rangers won. But when celtic beat rangers its cause they are great.. gerrard made a mistake first old firm of the season and played 5 centre midfielders and tried to contain celtic and we lost. But look at the 2 old firm games at ibrox last year, the cup final a few weeks back and that game there we dominated and its down to playing a high press and having a winger on. When we do that so fsr since gerrards been here celtic have no answers. The 2 park head defeats last yesr and the ibrox one this year have been games gerrards went to contain and not played wingers lol. Now hes realised wait if we press then high and attack they cant find options they cant get flowing and we dominate. So unless lennon finds out good tactics before the next 2 old firms to combat that style of play i think celtic will get dominated again in the next 2 old firms. And good luck to him trying to find tactics to shut out oursystem, same as liverpools system and no one in the premier lesgue with great managers has sussed them out yet

Since this has been uploaded by the SPFL I'd like to ask if they are happy with Clancy's performance.
The inconsistencies with the bookings and decisions were disgraceful.
Before he awarded Celtic the penalty there was shirt pulling by 2 Celtic players at a Rangers corner.
The first booking for Morelos was soft compared to some of the challenges that went before.
I could go on and on.
Absolute disgrace that the SPFL haven't commented on this poor poor performance of refereeing.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a fair man and I'd like to offer some advice to Celtic. Obvioulsy you're about to be knocked off your perch by Rangers so your only hope is to go cap in hand to Brendon Rogers and beg him to come back. He won't leave Leicester of course but I'm sure he could manage you on a part-time basis from his garden shed.
Christ almighty! You boys are in trouble. Steven Gerrard is building something big with those Rangers boys. I can see Rangers being big hitters in the Champions League in the near future and while they do, Celtic will be squabbling with Rod Stewart and crying about the potato famine.

snippet.textDisplay:
Rangers dominated Celtic, and I am not even Scottish, so I don't feel any kind of attachment to any of both teams, I am saying this with a neutral point of view.

I watched the game and that's what I saw, a team looking for the victory while Celtic was passing the ball uselessly from the defence to the midfield and vice-versa. Never trust the stats, watch the game.

This video's been cut by a Celtic fan, clearly.

Greetings from Spain, I love your country, and I really hope you get to play the Euro 2020 and beat England in Wembley.
